  <description type="2" xml:lang="EN">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Climate Iinvestment Platform (CIP) has been co-developed by the SEforALL, IRENA and UNDP, in coordination with the Green Climate Fund, which all are strategic partners for Danish development cooperation.
The development of this Start-up Phase programme came about following the launch of the Climate Investment Platform (CIP) in September 2019. During the period from October to December UNDP + CIP founding partners began the preparation of the draft concept note for the Start-up Phase.
The appraisal process has been informed by lessons learned from similar programmes and previous appraisals of similar projects/instruments by MFA and other stakeholders.
The Appraisal process kicked off in January 2020 after the development of a Process Action Plan (PAP) and the draft concept note being reviewed in the Ministry of Foreign Affairs (MFA) by the Sustainable Investments, jobs and Equal Opportunities unit (Gr&#xF8;nne Investering Jobs of Lige Muligheder, GJL) by both the Finance and Climate teams.
As part of the appraisal process for the Danida funded Start-up Phase programme, UNDP has coordinated a number of meetings between all stakeholders that has provided the opportunity for input to the development of the programme design and improvement of the programme documents. Draft documents were regularly circulated with all stakeholders and comments have been incorporated and addressed by UNDP. This process resulted in the submission of a draft programme document that in turn was subject to appraisal internally in MFA and in the Ministry of Climate, Energy and Utilities (Klima-, Energi og Forsyningsministeriet, KEFM). Following input from the two ministries, UNDP and GJL worked on incorporating comments and input into a further draft throughout March and April that culminated in the submission of the full package and completion of final program document, agreement and cover note in Mid-April.</narrative>
  </description>
